				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You have to remember when SoE makes spells they make a set number, and I for one want that number of spells to be useful for me to play my character. if they want fun spells make them a quest as in the fishing rod and ale you can get in PoP. That is a fun spells and it is a quest. When it comes to an expansion I do not want spells wasted on a fun spell when it should be something usable. 
<br />

<br />
As for voice graft etc.. that is a low level necro spell and some are seriously saying add it to the mage line up in an expansion? excuse me if I don't support that, make it a quest and yes I would do it most likely, but voice graft over a new pet heal? A new DD/rain spell, or even upgrades to the pet weapons/items? No thanks, I have enough useless spells as it is. Bundle as someone said, No one asks for it, and while I make a ton of arrows, rangers can also make them, and as for shrunkens monks can get the same effect at a lower level by a dropped item. Also how can arrows and shrunkens or daggers be considered fun items in any event?
<br />

<br />
I got Kunark the day it was released, and saw useless spells in abundance for us. A level 51 spell to make 20 bread/water/bandages in a 10 slot giant no weight bag. While I love the spell it is nowhere near a level 51 spell and yet that is when we got it. Many of us were pissed off at that, as it should be a sub 50 spell, as a natural progession to cornocopia and everfont, but we lost a spell slot to this spell. The daggers and shrunkens we got were also spells I wish we never got as no one asked for either of them, and wish I got something useful in exchange, like our pet heals in Kunark and not waiting to SoL was released to get a pet heal finally. 
<br />

<br />
Ask for fun spells and you LOSE useful spells. Want fun spells ask for them as a quest. I remember people asking for us to summon armour, and we got these fun spells. I never summon the leather, chain armour for anyone, and the plate I put on the pet occassionally, but leather and chain no one ever asks me to summon this for them. Ask for fun spells and as said, you get them and than they say Mage class done and move on, and we have a repeat of Kunark, SoV, and SoL. Ask for the mage class to gets fun spells, and you we will, namely the shaft.
<br />

<br />
Calebe</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
