				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My illustration was not a cut on devs at all. It was simply showing how asking for "fun" spells instead of "useful" spells might cause the devs to give us the fun ones instead of the useful ones.
<br />

<br />
Honestly, what do you expect from MS4? What I expect would probably be a version of Rathe's son with less hps and no proc. Sure it might have its place, but the fact remains that the mage community uses the air pet(or epic) about 80% of the time(from a grouping stand point). Why do we need yet another pet that is just "fun" but will never really come in handy?? I'd gladly give up the earth pet if they'd give us root. 
<br />

<br />
SOE isn't going to make our pets stronger, Im sure they have their balance reasons, so lets stop asking for more types of pets, we're already denied root because of the earth pet and stun because of the air pet. Why on earth do you want a pet without a proc? It could only be a downgrade. You know they aren't going to make it stronger than the other PoP pets and is probably why they never bothered to make MS4.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=705852" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Nucci</a>
