			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Nucci, ok let's talk cool factor and usefulness.  Let's talk what in actuality "could" be MS4 attributes and why those attributes "could" be an advantage.
<br />

<br />
Attributes:
<br />

<br />
*HP of Rathe's Son
<br />
*Damage per hit of Air
<br />
*Mitigation and Avoidance very close to Air
<br />
*Does not "cast" any spells therefore doesn't "waste" time against mobs that are immune to that attack, which is every boss mob. 
<br />
*DPS somewhere between Air pet and Water pet
<br />
*Potential High DS
<br />
*Fun Factor
<br />

<br />
Results:
<br />

<br />
*High HPs Excellent for soloing and off tanking
<br />

<br />
*Based on past MS line they have above average avoidance unlike their earthen cousin.  Combined with its HP could and most likely would make it better for off tanking and soloing than the other pets, unless stun or root were needed.
<br />

<br />
*Better than average DPS with better than average tanking make this pet the "hybrid" pet of choice, unless you need one of the other pets' special abilities.
<br />

<br />
*Potential for high DS can not be overlooked when considering LDoN adventures and soloing.  Even though I have ornate pants this would still be superior.
<br />

<br />
*This could easily be the pet of choice on mobs where say air pet's stun is ineffective (i.e. read doesn't work) where the pet doesn't waste its time casting therefore doing slightly better dps.
<br />

<br />
*Lastly, since the pet doesn't cast, more swings means more summoned weapon procs.  While this probably doens't mean much in DPS it means something over long periods.
<br />

<br />
Conclusion:
<br />

<br />
Although it would be situational, like the rest of our pets, it would give us the option to have a high HP pet like earth without the annoying root, with the ability to do greater damage than earth and most likely tank down mobs, due to mitigation, better than earth and at least as good air if not better; while doing better than average damage.  I don't find that marginal in the least, especially considering the fun factor of the spell.
<br />

<br />
Sorry you feel otherwise.  Please take my fire pet and replace it with MS4 since I never use that PoS anyway. <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" /><br />_________________<br />Sage Sarridon Soulcraver
<br />
Arch Convoker-Terris Thule</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
